To start your example of what you would like to do is not how a MasterDetailPage is meant to be used. To help here I&#39;ll illustrate with a simple example. The MasterDetailPage should never be wrapped inside of a NavigationPage, but rather the Detail of the MasterDetailPage should be a NavigationPage with some page set as its content.

    var page = new MasterDetailPage
    {
        Detail = new NavigationPage(new ContentPage())
    };

In Prism let&#39;s assume you have a MasterDetailPage called MainPage, and you&#39;ve registered the NavigationPage and a ContentPage called ViewA and another called ViewB.

The proper way of creating the MasterDetailPage would be:

    _navigationService.NavigateAsync(&quot;MainPage/NavigationPage/ViewA&quot;);

Now if you were to want to push ViewB from ViewA like:

    _navigationService.NavigateAsync(&quot;ViewB&quot;);

You would see this pushed inside of the NavigationPage with Navigation to go back to ViewA. Now let&#39;s say that you&#39;d like to force this to be a Modal you would simply do:

    _navigationService.NavigateAsync(&quot;ViewB?useModalNavigation=true&quot;);

